'''March 17''' is the 17th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshū|qid=Q96759839|1=senshū}}{{efn|ja|先勝|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 11th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1513|en|1513|qid=Q6200|lt=1513|1=1513}} {{ill|April 22|en|April 22|qid=Q2526|lt=April 22|1=April 22}}) – {{ill|Tachibana Dōsetsu|en|Tachibana Dōsetsu|qid=Q6379490|lt=Toyotachi Dōsetsu|1=Tachibana Dōsetsu}}, a military commander, was born (died {{ill|1585|en|1585|qid=Q6736|lt=1585|1=1585}} {{Sfn|楠戸|2009|p=165|qq=}}).

* {{ill|Kansei|en|Kansei|qid=Q1195131|lt=Kansei|1=Kansei}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1797|en|1797|qid=Q7820|lt=1797|1=1797}} {{ill|April 13|en|April 13|qid=Q2498|lt=April 13|1=April 13}}) – {{ill|Ōhara Yūgaku|en|Ōhara Yūgaku|qid=Q11433147|lt=Ōhara Yūgaku|1=Ōhara Yūgaku}}, an agricultural policy scholar, was born (died {{ill|1858|en|1858|qid=Q7684|lt=1858|1=1858}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1870|en|1870|qid=Q7741|lt=1870|1=1870}} {{ill|April 17|en|April 17|qid=Q2520|lt=April 17|1=April 17}}) – {{ill|Mitanmura Tobiyu|ja|三田村鳶魚|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitanmura Tobiyu|1=Engyo Mitamura|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11356752}}, an essayist and historian, was born (died {{ill|1952|en|1952|qid=Q5272|lt=1952|1=1952}}).
* 明治3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} 1870, {{ill|April 17|en|April 17|qid=Q2520|lt=April 17|1=April 17}}) – {{ill|Yanaguchi Naoma|ja|谷口尚真|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yanaguchi Naoma|1=Naomi Taniguchi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11632695}}, a military officer, was born (died {{ill|1941|en|1941|qid=Q5231|lt=1941|1=1941}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Taika (era)|en|Taika (era)|qid=Q1077930|lt=Taika|1=Taika (era)}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|649|en|649|qid=Q31117|lt=649|1=649}} {{ill|May 3|en|May 3|qid=Q2547|lt=May 3|1=May 3}}) – {{ill|Abenai Maro|ja|阿倍内麻呂|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abenai Maro|1=Abe no Uchimaro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11657240}}, a noble from the Asuka period (birth year unknown).
* {{ill|Daidō|en|Daidō|qid=Q1373191|lt=Daidō|1=Daidō}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|806|en|806|qid=Q30021|lt=806|1=806}} {{ill|April 9|en|April 9|qid=Q2504|lt=April 9|1=April 9}}) – {{ill|Emperor Kanmu|en|Emperor Kanmu|qid=Q314846|lt=Emperor Kanmu|1=Emperor Kanmu}}, the 50th Emperor of Japan (born {{ill|737|en|737|qid=Q411351|lt=737|1=737}}).
* {{ill|Ōhō|en|Ōhō|qid=Q1193927|lt=Ōhō|1=Ōhō}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1162|en|1162|qid=Q19667|lt=1162|1=1162}} {{ill|May 2|en|May 2|qid=Q2545|lt=May 2|1=May 2}}) – {{ill|Taira Motomori|ja|平基盛|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira Motomori|1=Q11482316|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11482316}}, a military commander of the Taira clan (born {{ill|1139|en|1139|qid=Q19608|lt=1139|1=1139}}).

